{"word":"ἄριστον","slug":"ἄριστον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἄριστον, ου, τό</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ἦρι</el> ‘early’ and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀριστάω\">ἀριστάω</a></el>] ‘occasion for eating’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> the early meal (as in Homeric usage) <b><i>breakfast</i> <a href='B:490 14:12'>Lk 14:12</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp> <i>midday/noon meal</i> <a href='B:470 22:4'>Mt 22:4</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp></b> in a general sense <b><i>meal</i> <a href='B:490 11:38'>Lk 11:38</a>; <a href='B:490 14:15'>14:15</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἀριστόβουλος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀρκετός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}